The Nigeria Export Processing Zones Authority (NEPZA) has described the appointment of the President of the Nigerian Association of Chambers of Commerce, Industry, Mines and Agriculture (NACCIMA), Chief John Udeagbala, to serve as an Ex-Officio member of the council of the ICC Chambers Federation as the country’s right moment to leverage on global investment opportunities. Managing Director of NEPZA, Prof. Adesoji Adesugba, in a congratulatory message, explained that Udeagbala’s appointment further confirmed his global networks, knowledge and capacity to help the body promote good corporate governance; business funding; foreign direct investments; and the growth of chambers across the world. Daily Trust reports that the ICC is a global forum connecting a global network of chambers and their businesses with 100 country members of the International Chambers of Commerce.